Question: read file from cache: :I have a file in cache and I want to read it. How can I do it?
Answer: <<<api>>>: $API
new Scanner(new FileInputStream(new File(getCacheDir(), "myFile")))
<<<code>>>: $CODE
Scanner scanner = new Scanner(new FileInputStream(new File(getCacheDir(), "myFile")));
while (scanner.hasNextLine()) {
    String line = scanner.nextLine();
    System.out.println(line);
}
scanner.close();
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION
In this code, we are using Scanner to read the file line by line. We are passing FileInputStream to Scanner which is reading from the file in cache directory.
```

Question: delete file from cache: :I have a file in cache and I want to delete it. How can I do it?
Answer: <<<api>>>: $API
new File(getCacheDir(), "myFile").delete()
<<<code>>>: $CODE
boolean success = new File(getCacheDir(), "myFile").delete();
if(success) {
    System.out.println("File deleted successfully");
} else {
    System.out.println("Failed to delete the file");
}
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION
In this code, we are using File.delete() method to delete the file from cache directory. It returns a boolean value indicating whether the file was successfully deleted or not.
```

Question: list files in cache: :I want to list all files in cache directory. How can I do it?
Answer: <<<api>>>: $API
new File(getCacheDir(), "*").listFiles()
<<<code>>>: $CODE
File[] files = new File(getCacheDir(), "*").listFiles();
for (File file : files) {
    if (file.isFile()) {
        System.out.println("File: " + file.getName());
    } else if (file.isDirectory()) {
        System.out.println("Directory: " + file.getName());
    }
}
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION
In this code, we are using File.listFiles() method to list all files and directories in cache directory. It returns an array of File objects. We are checking if each file is a file or a directory using File.isFile() and File.isDirectory() methods.
```

Question: move file from cache to another location: :I have a file in cache and I want to move it to another location. How can I do it?
Answer: <<<api>>>: $API
new File(getCacheDir(), "myFile").renameTo(new File(getExternalFilesDir(), "myFile"))
<<<code>>>: $CODE
boolean success = new File(getCacheDir(), "myFile").renameTo(new File(getExternalFilesDir(), "myFile"));
if(success) {
    System.out.println("File moved successfully");
} else {
    System.out.println("Failed to move the file");
}
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION
In this code, we are using File.renameTo() method to move the file from cache directory to another directory. It returns a boolean value indicating whether the file was successfully moved or not. In this case, we are moving the file to external files directory.
```

